-- BUZZ-Imtech drops to record low, outcome of debt talks awaited
-- 
-- Mon Aug 04, 2014 10:01AM EDT
-- None



AMSTERDAM, Aug 4 (Reuters) -    ** Shares in Dutch technical services company Imtech <IMUN.AS> lost another fifth of their value on Monday as details of any debt restructuring remained elusive.

** Last week the company said it was in talks with lenders & that it had seen no improvement in its business in the second quarter. [ID:nL6N0Q644L]  ** KBC Securities analyst Dirk Verbiesen says uncertainty on outcome of talks a key worry as company is highly leveraged.  ** Debt to equity ratio stands at 2.98, easily the highest among peers, according to StarMine. ** Sale of the ICT division is on track according to the company & a successful disposal could help to reduce debt. ** Stock is down nearly 80% this year.  ($1 = 0.7450 Euros)   (RM: jussi.rosendahl.thomsonreuters.com@reuters.net)  Keywords: MARKETS EUROPE STOCKSNEWS